Introduction

Sohee was a South Korean singer, actress, and model managed by IOK Company. She first gained attention by placing second on KPOP Star 6. She debuted as the main vocalist, lead dancer, and face of the girl group ALICE (formerly known as Elris). During her early career, Sohee was highly anticipated to be her generation's "IT girl."

On October 18, 2018, she released her first solo digital single, "Hurry Up".

On April 26, 2024, Sohee announced her engagement to a non-celebrity businessman, who is 15 years her senior, after dating for a year. With her marriage announcement, she also declared her retirement from the entertainment industry. Her contract with IOK Company was set to expire around the same time, marking the end of her career with ALICE and in K-pop.
